  Harbour & Field Size Table Snippet
  Accessible size measurement table for shirts
{% endcomment %}

<table class="hf-size-table" role="table" aria-label="Shirt size measurements">
  <caption class="sr-only">Shirt measurements in centimeters</caption>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th scope="col" class="hf-size-table-header">Size</th>
      <th scope="col" class="hf-size-table-header">Chest (cm)</th>
      <th scope="col" class="hf-size-table-header">Neck (cm)</th>
      <th scope="col" class="hf-size-table-header">Sleeve (cm)</th>
      <th scope="col" class="hf-size-table-header">Length (cm)</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <th scope="row" class="hf-size-table-row-header">XS</th>
      <td class="hf-size-table-cell">86–90</td>
      <td class="hf-size-table-cell">35–36</td>
      <td class="hf-size-table-cell">82</td>
      <td class="hf-size-table-cell">71</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th scope="row" class="hf-size-table-row-header">S</th>
      <td class="hf-size-table-cell">92–96</td>
      <td class="hf-size-table-cell">37–38</td>
      <td class="hf-size-table-cell">84</td>
      <td class="hf-size-table-cell">73</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th scope="row" class="hf-size-table-row-header">M</th>
      <td class="hf-size-table-cell">97–101</td>
      <td class="hf-size-table-cell">39–40</td>
      <td class="hf-size-table-cell">86</td>
      <td class="hf-size-table-cell">75</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th scope="row" class="hf-size-table-row-header">L</th>
      <td class="hf-size-table-cell">102–106</td>
      <td class="hf-size-table-cell">41–42</td>
      <td class="hf-size-table-cell">88</td>
      <td class="hf-size-table-cell">77</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th scope="row" class="hf-size-table-row-header">XL</th>
      <td class="hf-size-table-cell">107–112</td>
      <td class="hf-size-table-cell">43–44</td>
      <td class="hf-size-table-cell">90</td>
      <td class="hf-size-table-cell">79</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th scope="row" class="hf-size-table-row-header">XXL</th>
      <td class="hf-size-table-cell">113–118</td>
      <td class="hf-size-table-cell">45–46</td>
      <td class="hf-size-table-cell">92</td>
      <td class="hf-size-table-cell">81</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<div class="hf-size-guide-note">
  <p><strong>How to measure:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Chest:</strong> Measure around the fullest part of your chest, under your arms</li>
    <li><strong>Neck:</strong> Measure around the base of your neck where the collar sits</li>
    <li><strong>Sleeve:</strong> From the center back of your neck to your wrist</li>
    <li><strong>Length:</strong> From the base of the collar to the bottom hem</li>
  </ul>
  <p><em>If you're between sizes, we recommend sizing up for a more comfortable fit.</em></p>
</div>
